.SH NAME
\fB²DPROG² \- PZN from BDT\fR: extracts medication plan PDFs embedded in BDT files and completes PZN/active ingredient/trade name in the medication plan
.br
(manpage-Hilfe in deutsch verfügbar: 'man ²DPROG²' oder 'man -Lde ²DPROG²')
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fB²DPROG² [-<shortopt>|--<longopt> [<supplement>]] ...\fR
.SH SHORT DESCRIPTION
\fB²DPROG²\fR is a command line program that scans the BDT files exported by the practice management system (TurboMed) in the directory \fBbdtvz\fR (default: \fB/DATA/eigene Dateien/TMExport\fR) for sections indicating a printout of a standardised German medication plan (BMP, "AMTS:MP").
.br
If such a printout is found, the referenced PDF file is determined, split with positional accuracy into text using \fBpdftotext -bbox\fR, and for each medication line the active ingredient, trade name and national medication code (PZN) are reconstructed.
.br
These triples are recorded in the table \fBbdtnachw\fR and additionally used to complete matching, still incomplete entries in the medication plan (table \fBmedplan\fR) with active ingredient, trade name and initial letter, based on the PZN.
.br
The program is suited for the retroactive enrichment of medication plan entries imported via BDT that lack the structured PZN assignment.
.SH INSTALLATION
.br
First, please read the chapters 'Functionality', 'Preconditions', 'Automatically installed software packages' and 'Implications' below. Then, if connected to the internet, call (e.g. by copying the line and pasting it into a terminal):
.br
\fBN=²DPROG²;P=${N}_inst.sh;cd ~;wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/²gitv²/$N/master/install.sh -O$P&&sh $P\fR
.br
At last, call:
.br
 \fB²DPROG²\fR
.br
and answer some questions of the program.
.SH USAGE
Ideally, the program should have installed itself after the first call(s) and one-time answering of some questions in a self-running way.
.br
The program is typically called periodically via \fBcron\fR (option \fB-cm\fR/\fB--cronminutes\fR). At each call, only BDT files not yet recorded (with the same modification date) in the table \fBbdtdat\fR are processed.
.br
\fB-nd\fR/\fB--nurdatei\fR restricts processing to a single specified file (e.g. for testing); \fB-d\fR/\fB--delete\fR clears all bdt tables beforehand to force a complete re-run.
