.SH FUNCTIONALITY
.LP
When called, '\fB²DPROG²\fR' accomplishes the following:
.LP
\fB1)\fR General and program-specific defaults are set.
.LP
\fB2)\fR Defaults are loaded from the configuration file, if it exists (default: \fB²DPROG².conf\fR in the same directory as \fB²DPROG²\fR, default: \fB/usr/local/sbin/²DPROG²\fR).
.LP
\fB3)\fR Command line arguments are evaluated and override the configuration file where applicable.
.LP
\fB4)\fR Questions are asked if values are missing or an interactive option is set.
.LP
\fB5)\fR The program inserts itself if wanted and necessary into root's \fBcrontab\fR in order to be called in adjustable intervals.
.LP
\fB6)\fR The MariaDB database is initialised; the tables \fBbdtdat\fR (processed files), \fBbdtpdf\fR (referenced PDF files) and \fBbdtnachw\fR (extracted PZN/active ingredient/trade name assignments) are checked and if necessary created or amended (in this order because of foreign keys). With \fB-d\fR (\fB--delete\fR) they are cleared beforehand.
.LP
\fB7)\fR The directory \fBbdtvz\fR is searched for BDT files (with \fB-nd\fR only the specified one); files already recorded in \fBbdtdat\fR with the same modification date are skipped.
.LP
\fB8)\fR Each new BDT file is scanned line by line. Based on fixed field markers (among others \fB3000\fR for the patient ID, \fB6298CreationDate\fR/\fB6298CreationTime\fR, and a state machine over the markers \fB6299\fR with "AMTS:MP", \fB6298IsPrinted\fR, \fB6298OriginalFormat\fR, \fB6298PDFFilePath\fR and \fB6324\fR) it is detected whether and where a printed medication plan ("#CGM BMP gedruckt#") is referenced.
.LP
\fB9)\fR The associated PDF file is determined from the referenced path (umlaut back-conversion, base directory \fB/DATA/turbomed\fR) and, if not yet present, recorded in \fBbdtpdf\fR.
.LP
\fB10)\fR The PDF file is converted to position-annotated text with \fBpdftotext -bbox\fR. Based on the x/y coordinates of the text fragments, rows of the medication table and their columns "active ingredient" and "trade name" are reconstructed; in parallel, the corresponding PZN per row are taken from the original BDT section.
.LP
\fB11)\fR If the number of recognised PZN matches the number of recognised medication rows, a record is inserted into \fBbdtnachw\fR for each row (unless excluded by \fB-d\fR) (patient ID, PDF reference, date, medication, active ingredient, PZN, among others).
.LP
\fB12)\fR If the recognised medication name is not "UNBEKANNTE" ("unknown"), the matching, still incomplete entry in the table \fBmedplan\fR is additionally completed with trade name, initial letter and active ingredient, based on the PZN.
.LP
\fB13)\fR For all patients thus updated, the stored procedure \fBfuellThaP\fR is finally called to adjust their therapy types.
.LP
\fB14)\fR The configuration file is written if necessary.
.LP
\fB15)\fR If the option \fB-autoupd\fR is active, the program's version number is compared with that of the installation source and, if behind, an update is performed.
.SH PRECONDITIONS
\fBHardware\fR: Access to the directory with the practice management system's BDT export files as well as to the PDF documents referenced therein (default base directory \fB/DATA/turbomed\fR).
.br
\fBSoftware\fR: The program is adjusted to an installation of Opensuse >= 42.1, Debian >= 9, Ubuntu >= 16.04, Mint >= 18 or Fedora >= 24 with standard options. System D must be installed. One of the packet managers \fBapt\fR, \fBdnf\fR, \fByum\fR or \fBzypper\fR must be installed. The program '\fBwget\fR' must be installed. MariaDB must be running. \fBpoppler-utils\fR (command line tool \fBpdftotext\fR) is required for PDF analysis.
.SH AUTOMATICALLY INSTALLED SOFTWARE PACKAGES
.br
(for this purpose, depending on the distribution, zypper, apt(-get), dnf or yum are used).
.LP
