.br
acl, boost, boost-devel, boost-locale, cron, mariadb-server, poppler-tools (resp. poppler-utils)
.SH IMPLICATIONS
The program has to take the following measures for its neat function:
.LP
\fB1)\fR Sudo (is missing per default in debian) will be installed if needed.
.br
The current linux user, if not already contained, will be entered into an administrator group mentioned in /etc/sudoers.
.LP
\fB2)\fR 'GNU make' will be installed if not present, automatically by calling 'sh install.sh'.
.LP
\fB3)\fR Creation of a logfile, per default \fB/var/log/²DPROG².log\fR.
.LP
\fB4)\fR Creation and adjustment of the configuration file \fB²DPROG².conf\fR in the program directory (default: \fB/usr/local/sbin/\fR).
.LP
\fB5)\fR Insertion of a line for the periodic automatic program call in root's crontab (if configured).
.LP
\fB6)\fR Creation of the configured database and the tables \fBbdtdat\fR, \fBbdtpdf\fR, \fBbdtnachw\fR in MariaDB, if necessary; if necessary insertion of a MariaDB user.
.LP
\fB7)\fR Modification of existing entries in the table \fBmedplan\fR (completion of medication, initial letter and active ingredient for rows uniquely identifiable via PZN).
.SH UNINSTALLING
Change in a terminal to the installation directory (for the same installed user, it's \fBcd ~/²DPROG²\fR, otherwise it will be displayed by \fB²DPROG² -info\fR).
.br
Call \fBmake uninstall\fR.
.br
Then the installed \fB²DPROG²\fR will be deleted and the script \fBuninstallinv\fR will be executed in reverse order which has been generated during the installation and execution of ²DPROG².
.br
Thereby additionally installed program packets and permissions are deleted.
.br
Configuration files, accumulated data and system relevant programs will not be deleted.
.br
Error messages originate mostly in efforts to delete a program already missing and can then be ignored.
.SH RETURN CODES
\fB0\fR: Normal return code
.br
\fB7\fR: The info screen (\fB²DPROG² -info\fR) has been displayed
.br
\fB8\fR: The help has been displayed
.br
\fB10\fR: Initializing of the database failed and the program was stopped therefore
.br
\fB11\fR: Checking of a database table failed and the program was stopped therefore
.br
\fB98\fR: Program stopped because it is already running once
.br
\fB113\fR: An sql command for the mariadb database failed with a miscellaneous error
.br
\fB115\fR: A database entry failed because of a full disk
.br
After calling \fB²DPROG² -vi\fR or \fB²DPROG² -vs\fR the return code of \fBvi\fR/\fBvim\fR will be passed
